\end_inset

The State Capacity Ceiling on Tax Rates: Evidence from Randomized Tax Abatements
 in the DRC
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Bergeron, Tourek & Weigel (2021): Motivation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
How much revenue can be raised, and the welfare effect of taxation is determined
 by fiscal capacity
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In the Besley & Persson formulation, fiscal capacity reduces the elasticity
 of the tax base by making it costlier to evade.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the elasticity of the tax base goes down, then the revenue-maximizing
 (Laffer) rate goes up
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conduct a field experiment to test these ideas.
 Exploit experimental variation in 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
tax abatements (= tax rates?)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
tax enforcement (letters, more/less effective tax collectors)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Bergeron, Tourek & Weigel (2021): Setting
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Experiment conducted in Kanaga, a large (1M pop) city in DRC.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Median monthly HH income in Kananga is $106.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DRC ranked 188th out of 200 in terms of tax/GDP
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Property tax campaign in 2018 in two steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Registration visit: tell property owners about the property tax, assess
 high or low band property, exemption.
 Gave owner a letter with (randomly) assigned tax rate
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Follow-up visits to collect the tax.
 Given one month to pay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Randomly assigned tax rates stratifying by neighborhood and tax band.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

